<title>
MAF and IAT Sensor Inspection
</title>
<ptxt>
<intxrefpoff refid = "AENAP70B1306025">MAF and IAT Sensor Removal and Installation</intxrefpoff>
</ptxt>
<servinfosub id = "AENAP70B1306026001" page = "2">
<title>
IAT Sensor Inspection
</title>
<attention2>
<list1 type = "unordered">
<item>
<ptxt>
When servicing MAF and IAT sensor, be sure to observe the following precautions.
</ptxt>
</item>
<list2 type = "unordered">
<item>
<ptxt>
Do not disassemble MAF and IAT sensor.
</ptxt>
</item>
<item>
<ptxt>
Do not drop or expose MAF and IAT sensor to any shock. Any sensor that has been dropped must be replaced.
</ptxt>
</item>
<item>
<ptxt>
Do not clean MAF and IAT sensor.
</ptxt>
</item>
<item>
<ptxt>
Do not blow compressed air to MAF and IAT sensor using air blow gun or the like.
</ptxt>
</item>
<item>
<ptxt>
Do not put finger or any other object into MAF and IAT sensor.
</ptxt>
</item>
</list2>
<item>
<ptxt>
Do not heat MAF and IAT sensor to temperature higher than 100 &#176;C (212 &#176;F). MAF and IAT sensor will be damaged if heated to higher temperatures.
</ptxt>
</item>
</list1>
</attention2>
<s1 page = "2">
<ptxt>
Remove MAF and IAT sensor. 
<intxreftitleoff1 refid = "AENAP70B1306025"><img src = "..\icon\intxreftitleoff.gif"/></intxreftitleoff1>
</ptxt>
</s1>
<s1 page = "2">
<ptxt>
Check sensor O-ring (1) for damage and deterioration. Replace if necessary.
</ptxt>
</s1>
<s1 page = "2">
<ptxt>
Check that resistance between sensor terminals varies depending on temperature while blowing hot air to temperature sensing part (2) of MAF and IAT sensor (3) using hot air drier (4).
</ptxt>
<ptxt>
If faulty condition is found, replace MAF and IAT sensor. 
<intxreftitleoff1 refid = "AENAP70B1306025"><img src = "..\icon\intxreftitleoff.gif"/></intxreftitleoff1>
</ptxt>
